Element idf:entrySet / idf:entry

Annotations
 
Describes one or more structural states of one or more regions as a 
self-contained unit. Multiple entries from different files can be concatenated into a 
single entrySet. Grouping within an entry will likely be based on publication or protein.

Element idf:xref / idf:primaryRef
Namespace http://psi.hupo.org/id/idf100
Annotations
 
Primary reference to an external database.
Diagram
Type idf:dbReference
Properties
content: complex
Model idf:attributeList
Children idf:attributeList
Instance
 
<idf:primaryRef db="" dbAc="" id="" refType="" refTypeAc="" secondary="" version="" xmlns:idf="http://psi.hupo.org/id/idf100">
  <idf:attributeList>{1,1}</idf:attributeList>
</idf:primaryRef>
Attributes
QName Type Fixed Default Use Annotation
db restriction of xs:string required 
Name of the external database, taken from the controlled vocabulary of 
databases.
dbAc restriction of xs:string optional 
Accession number of the database in the database CV. This element is 
controlled by the PSI-MI CV "database citation", root term id MI:0444.
id restriction of xs:string required 
Primary identifier of the object in the external database, e.g. UniProt accession number.
refType restriction of xs:string optional 
Reference type, e.g. "identity" if this reference refers to an identical object 
in the external database, or "see-also" for additional information, using a term from PSI-MI CV, 
root term cross-reference type (MI:0353).
refTypeAc restriction of xs:string optional 
Reference type accession number from the CV of reference types. This element is 
controlled by the PSI-MI CV "xref type", root term id MI:0353.
secondary restriction of xs:string optional 
Secondary identifier of the object in the external database, e.g. UniProt ID.
version restriction of xs:string optional 
The version number of the object in the external database.
Source
 
<xs:element name="primaryRef" type="idf:dbReference">
  <xs:annotation>
    <xs:documentation>Primary reference to an external database.</xs:documentation>
  </xs:annotation>
</xs:element>

Element idf:source / idf:xref
Namespace http://psi.hupo.org/id/idf100
Annotations
 
Unambiguous identification of the source by a CV term; for instance, 
the primary reference with attributes db="psi-mi" dbAc="MI:0488" id="MI:1332" refType=
"identity" refTypeAc="MI:0356" refers to source bhf-ucl, which is identical to term 
MI:1332 in PSI-MI CV, which lists itself as term MI:0488. For this we need to define 
similar PSI-ID CV terms.

    <xs:sequence>

      </xs:element>

          <xs:annotation>

In combination with the numeric value, the attribute 'status' allows to express fuzzy positions, e.g. 'more than 400'. Negative positions can be used to describe promotor regions but should not be allowed for proteins</xs:documentation>
          </xs:annotation>
        </xs:element>
        <xs:element name="endInterval" type="idf:interval">
          <xs:annotation>
            <xs:documentation>The end position may be varying or unclear, but localisable to a certain range. Usually written as e.g. 3..5. Negative positions can be used to describe promotor regions but should not be allowed for proteins</xs:documentation>
          </xs:annotation>

      </xs:choice>
    </xs:sequence>

'begin' references the first amino acid, 'end' the second. Standard example is a disulfide bridge.
